About
Considered an oasis in the centre of Lisbon, this is one of the city’s best gardens and a favourite of its inhabitants. In 2023, the grounds will extend to 8. 000 m2 of green spaces as part of the landscape renovation of the Centro de Arte Moderna, designed by Vladimir Djurovic.
Duration: 1-2 hours

Allan T
Toronto, Canada111 contributions
A garden oasis, a beautiful museum
May 2023
Old, tourist Lisbon is wonderful, but also congested with tourists and the ubiquitous hills and cobblestone streets can wear you down in the heat. This museum and its garden is an oasis I strongly recommend. It's a short metro ride to a spacious, upscale part of town and next to the Park (also worth seeing). The gardens is free, full of lush scenery, streams and ducks. They are also many places to sit. It is clean. Rest your feet, nap and eat a sandwich here in peace. The permanent exhibition costs 10 Euros and is worth it, if you like seeing objects of beauty from around the world like Persian rugs, Armenian parchments and paintings by Turner and Manet. Spacious and not jammed like the big museums of, say, Paris. Staff are friendly. Cafe is affordable and offers a patio facing the garden. Would definitely return.
Review of: Calouste Gulbenkian Museum Admission Ticket
Written May 24, 2023
